title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Sauer - Sig556 Rifle, NEW IN BOX, New Gun Legislation TODAY
postcontent:
The Sig Sauer 556 Classic is a semi-automatic centerfire rifle made by the SigArms company in Exeter, NH. The gas-piston system of this rifle is similar to the AK-47, it uses a gas port forward in the barrel to force a long piston op-rod backwards; discharging the casing and loading a new round. The gas system has two settings, both of them appear to be of the same port size (providing a dirty-port alternative; in case of a gas system failure)

It’s chambered in .223/5.56mm and has a 1 in 7″ twist rate barrel. It’s capable of using AR-15 type magazines that are widely available in a range of capacities. The rifle has an “HK-Style” sight system (rotary distance adjustable rear, post-in-ring up front) with an additional rear sight integrated into the rail system (emergency backup only; it’s a very flimsy piece of hinged steel). The rifle has ambidextrous safety selectors, and an AR-15 style magazine release.

The grip angle is a bit more swept back, and a longer reach to the safety selector, than the AR-15. The reciprocating charging handle is located on the right side of the weapon, directly attached to the bolt. The trigger is a two-stage of pull, that breaks cleanly and evenly with repeatable first stage take-up every time. The Stock is a plastic Swiss-Style side folder, similar to that of the Sig SG 550 rifles. The bold hold/release is in a similar location to the AR-15, but operates on an extended pivot system comparatively.

Comes with:

1 -Sig 556 Rifle
1 -Box
1 -Paperwork
1 -30rd Metal Sig Sauer Mag
1 -30rd Lancer Smoke colored mag (in picture)
1 -Extended safety lever (factory safety lever included as well)
1 -Swiss Bayonet with scabbard and Lug (installed)

Make me a CASH offer. I want this GONE TODAY.

title: For Sale:  GUN - KNIFE - COIN FLASH AUCTION IN FLORENCE ONLINE THURS JAN 3 8PM - NO RESERVES
postcontent:
This coming Thursday night at 8PM sharp, I will be having a flash auction on the local website www.ShoalsGunEnthusiasts.com. Anyone can have them there, this just happens to be one of mine. I will be selling WITHOUT RESERVE a home defense shotgun, several knives, a collection of silver money, some watches and other things mantique related. This type of auction was developed and has matured in our facebook group "Shoals Gun Enthusiasts" and we run them there all the time. The way it works is We post an item for sale and the people reply to the post with bids. The item is only offered for a couple of minutes so the bidding is live and it is similar to having a live auction with absentee bidders bidding on the internet at it. 

YOU MUST be registered on the site (which is free) to be able to post and bid. The payment is typically done in person since it is mostly local but if you are out of the area, I can take paypal and ship to you, that is fine. I am not worried about what the items bring, but you be SURE if you bid and win, you complete the transaction with me. It is your responsibility to get up with me and get your merchandise or pay me for the shipping...

If you are the winner of the shotgun (which is my personal weapon), you need to be certain you are legally able to buy one. While I am not taking it to someplace to transfer through an FFL unless you live out of state, I will be writing a bill of sale and we will sign it to cover my tooter :-)

It is a lot of fun and the members we have on the FB group (1450 of them) love doing these. The website was just setup this past weekend so there isn't a lot of competition for you on the stuff yet, its a good time to get in on some bidding. There is also several discussion forums, a timed auction there and classifieds so you can post your for sale or wanted items.
